Title: A new method to measure the chiral condensate in lattice QCD using
  Wilson fermions
Authors: Khalil M. Bitar, Urs M. Heller, Rajamani Narayanan
Comments: 9 pages, LaTeX, no figures
Report-no: FSU-SCRI-97-112
Journal-ref: Phys.Lett. B418 (1998) 167-172
\\
  Parity and flavor symmetry is not broken in QCD. Using this fact, we propose
a new method to measure the chiral condensate in lattice QCD using Wilson
fermions with an operator that breaks parity and flavor in addition to the
chiral symmetry.
